The paper deals with the problem of recovering a sparse signal from compressed samples in the presence of noise, which is a fundamental problem in information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely categories. The paper also presents theoretical results on the number of measurements required for recovery, which involves analyzing the performance of different recovery algorithms. This suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also relevant categories. Finally, the paper uses techniques from numerical analysis and optimization to analyze the recovery algorithms, which suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also a possible category.
